[{"id":"VR814808","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a sphere of mass m hanging from a string attached to a ceiling. The string slants downward and to the right at an angle of theta from the vertical. An electric field is formed and indicated by horizontal lines with arrows pointing to the right.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR814808.g02.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A sphere of charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"q\"><math alttext=\"q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>q</mi></math></span></span> and mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m\"><math alttext=\"m\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>m</mi></math></span></span> hangs from a string attached to the ceiling. An electric field is established in the area where the sphere hangs, causing the sphere to move to a new position such that the string makes an angle <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta\"><math alttext=\"theta\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>θ</mi></math></span></span> with the vertical, as shown in the figure. What is the magnitude of the electric field?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR814808_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator m g times the tangent of theta, and denominator q\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator m g times the tangent of theta, and denominator q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi>tan</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow><mi>q</mi></mfrac></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator m g times the sine of theta, and denominator q\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator m g times the sine of theta, and denominator q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi>sin</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow><mi>q</mi></mfrac></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator m g, and denominator q times the cosine of theta, end fraction\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator m g, and denominator q times the cosine of theta, end fraction\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>q</mi><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi>cos</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator m g, and denominator q\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator m g, and denominator q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow><mi>q</mi></mfrac></mstyle></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":0}]